title: Russian rock band that protested war may be deported to Moscow by Thailand
description: Members of the Russian rock band, Bi-2, which spoke out against the war, are under arrest in Thailand. Supporters fear Russia is demanding they be expelled to Moscow.

title: Israeli document alleges U.N. workers took part in Oct. 7 Hamas attack
description: The Israeli dossier says 13 UNRWA employees played a role in the attacks, including six who infiltrated into Israel.

title: Sandra Milo, who played mistress in Federico Fellini’s ‘8½,’ dies at 90
description: Offscreen, Ms. Milo recounted her 17-year secret love affair with the director in her book “Caro Federico.”

title: French farmers encircle Paris with an angry blockade
description: French farmers deployed their tractors to choke major highways, disrupting not only trade and traffic, but also politics and normal life, to protest subsidy cuts and new regulations.

title: Why pro-Iran militias are attacking U.S. troops in Iraq, Jordan, Syria
description: The Islamic Resistance in Iraq and other pro-Iran groups have launched 160 attacks against U.S. troops in Iraq and Syria since the Israel-Gaza war broke out.

title: U.S. weighs response to killing of its troops in tinderbox Middle East
description: With American blood now spilled, deterrence is expected to be more robust, raising the danger of further escalation in a region where conflict is already in full swing in several places.

title: Catherine, Princess of Wales, leaves the hospital after abdominal surgery
description: The future queen is expected to need a significant period of time to recover. She isn’t scheduled to return to her official duties until after Easter.

title: ‘Collective rapes’ surge as weapon in Haiti’s gang war
description: The armed gangs that are terrorizing Haiti have revived the use of rape to instill fear and punish local populations. For survivors, support is inadequate and justice elusive.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Biden vows response after drone strike kills 3 U.S. troops in Jordan
description: Thirty-four service members were also injured in the attack, which President Biden blamed on militant groups supported by Iran.

title: Ukraine’s hopes for victory over Russia are slipping away
description: Some think the West may have already squandered its best chance to enable Ukraine to fully liberate its territory.

title: China’s Evergrande, owing more than $300 billion, ordered to liquidate
description: It is unclear whether China will comply with the Hong Court’s ruling against the property behemoth, but the decision will compound fears about the Chinese economy.
